  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protecting and assisting refugees and asylum seekers, migrants and trafficking victims</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With the aim of building up Israel as a just, equitable and democratic society in which the human rights of all people are honoured, Hotline for Refugees and Migrants (HRM) strives to extend a comprehensive programme of assistance and protection for refugees and asylum seekers, migrant workers and trafficking victims.  Services include a telephone hotline, regular visits to detention centres, provision of information, legal advice and representation, data collection and monitoring of the treatment of migrant workers, High Court petitions and promoting enforcement of the rule of law, campaigning and advocacy work with decision-makers, media, non-governmental agencies and the general public.  HRM&#x2019;s knowledge and experience are widely recognised as making it an authority on issues concerned refugees and migrants, and it serves as an advisory body for national and international bodies, government ministries, academia and civic organizations.</narrative>
  </description>
